    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nModule size matters to many users, and the storage size of strings can make a difference.\nSince https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6971, we store strings compressed, but use `zlib` by default.\nIn some Python installations, especially very constrained containers, the `zlib` module might not be available, so that importing a Cython module that used `zlib` for its string compression will fail.\n\nThus, we will have to turn compression off by default if we do not find a safely self-contained replacement.\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\n[FastLZ](https://ariya.github.io/FastLZ/) is a very small single-file compressor and decompressor implementation. It features two slightly different implementations for different compression levels. The two corresponding decompressors are very short:\n\nhttps://github.com/ariya/FastLZ/blob/b1342dabcf5257ab303743c9332fe75e9147a011/fastlz.c#L283-L320\nhttps://github.com/ariya/FastLZ/blob/b1342dabcf5257ab303743c9332fe75e9147a011/fastlz.c#L429-L480\n\nWe should try to replace the current default compression for Cython modules with FastLZ.\n\nThe disadvantage is that the current compressor implementation is written in C, which creates a dependency on C code. Cython can currently run from its Python sources without any setup, and uses pure Python wheel installations on some platforms.\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\nTurn off compression by default and require users to enable it themselves according to their needs.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
