            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> The disadvantage is that the current compressor implementation is written in C, which creates a dependency on C code. \n\nThere are implementations in python -e.g. https://github.com/julyanserra/Basic-LZ77-in-Python\n\nThey seems to be short. Maaybe we can vendor it? Not sure about license it is not mentioned and the overhead having it vendor. It is short - 80 lines of python code and performance should be reasonable since we are not compressing megabytes...\n\nBut keep it with huge grain of salt I haven't tried the library so I am not sure how good it is...",
